%section#commission
  .container
    %h2
      Who pays?
    %p
      There are two kinds of projects available to Uplink members:
    %h3
      Commission paid by the client
    %p
      For many projects, we are able to negotiate a commission directly with the client. Only after the freelancer has begun the project and both parties are satisfied with it’s progress is the company billed for our service. For freelancers, this means the commission is handled entirely between the client and Uplink.
    %h3
      Commission paid by the freelancer
    %p
      Some clients have a policy to not work with services that charge a commission. Still, these clients might offer very attractive projects - a good hourly rate, remote work, technologically interesting etc. - and of course we’d like to make these projects available to you.
    %p
      This is why for such projects we ask the freelancer to pay a
      %strong
        monthly fee of 10% of their earnings, capped at 1,500€ total.
      Many of our members simply incorporate this fee into their hourly rate, so they don't even notice it.
    %p
      By being flexible and not insisting on charging a commission to each client, Uplink becomes a very attractive option to them: it costs them the same as posting the project on a online job board, but they get a much better service.
      %strong
        That way we can maximise the number of projects available to our members.

